<POST>
<POSTER> TaliesinSoft &lt;taliesins...@mac.com&gt; </POSTER>
<POSTDATE> 2007-07-23T00:20:00 </POSTDATE>
I recently encountered issues with two applications which I literally run
every day, SuperDuper! and Hogwasher.

In both cases I reported in detail the issues I encountered to the suppliers
of the aforementioned applications, Shirt-Pocket for SuperDuper! and Asar for
Hogwasher.

I received a response from Shirt-Pocket within the hour. Although a number of
days have passed I have yet to even receive an acknowledgment from Asar.

I am a strong proponent of both SuperDuper! and Hogwasher, but find myself
perplexed at the difference in support provided.

--
James Leo Ryan ..... Austin, Texas ..... taliesins ... @mac.com
