The following three statements are from the Hogwasher help file....

==========

Symptom: &quot;An unknown error has occurred&quot;

Explanation: The MacOS has reported an error that is not in Hogwasher's
defined list of errors.

Solution: Please choose Technical Support in the Hogwasher menu and include
the error code, a description of what you were doing when the error occurred,
and the Technical Support information (see above). We will assist you in
determining the cause of the error and an appropriate course of action.

==========

When the crashing occurred I did use the Technical Support option and
included a description of what I was doing at the moment of the crash and
included a copy of the Hogwasher crash log. This was done several times
without any response.

