Having received no response from Asar regarding my Hogwasher problem,
immediate crashing upon an attempt to read a given subscription, I finally
totally trashed Hogwasher and all of its files and then reinstalled Hogwasher
and rebuilt my subscriptions, an action that eliminated the crashing. However
this was an action I preferred to not do, but in desperation finally forced
myself to do. It did cure the problem, but at the expense of losing my
history. Whether or not there could have been a less violent solution could
likely have been answered if Asar bothered to respond to my request for help.

There have often been grumps posted in these discussions that Hogwasher is
high priced for a newsreader. One would expect that part of what you are
paying for is the support I did not receive.

